column2: print("The graph that I chose is a boxplot that depicts the IQ data by the variable, Smelter, which consists of two categories: far and near. From the boxplot, we can see that the far category has a few outliers but one clear outlier that is not an accurate representation of an individual's IQ. An IQ of 131 or greater is considered very superior (https://www.healthline.com/health/what-is-considered-a-high-iq#whats-a-high-iq). Thus, an IQ of 1000 is likely a data entry error or some other type of error. The table is a simple representation of the median of IQ for each category. The median of the far smelter is 93 and the mean of the near smelter is about 88.")

"The graph that I chose is a boxplot that depicts the IQ data by the variable, Smelter, which consists of two categories: far and near. From the boxplot, we can see that the far category has a few outliers but one clear outlier that is not an accurate representation of an individual's IQ. An IQ of 131 or greater is considered very superior (https://www.healthline.com/health/what-is-considered-a-high-iq#whats-a-high-iq). Thus, an IQ of 1000 is likely a data entry error or some other type of error. The table is a simple representation of the median of IQ for each category. The median of the far smelter is 93 and the mean of the near smelter is about 88."
